# Line-ending policy for cross-platform clones (repo is Windows-authored).
# Text files are stored LF in the repo and checked out per-platform, except
# where an explicit eol is forced below.
* text=auto

# Shell scripts run on the Linux VM (scraper-vm) -- force LF so a Windows
# checkout's CRLF can never break the shebang or the script when scp'd over.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Windows-only launchers: force CRLF everywhere (cmd.exe needs CRLF for
# multi-line scripts; PowerShell 5.1 is safest with CRLF).
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Binary assets: never diff, merge, or normalize.
*.png binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
